31bool CanInlinePropertyAccess(MapRef map, AccessMode access_mode) {
32 // We can inline property access to prototypes of all primitives, except
33 // the special Oddball ones that have no wrapper counterparts (i.e. Null,
34 // Undefined and TheHole).
35 // We can only inline accesses to dictionary mode holders if the access is a
36 // load and the holder is a prototype. The latter ensures a 1:1
37 // relationship between the map and the object (and therefore the property
38 // dictionary).
39 static_assert(ODDBALL_TYPE == LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE);
40 if (IsBooleanMap(*map.object())) return true;
41 if (map.instance_type() < LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE) return true;
42 if (IsJSObjectMap(*map.object())) {
43 if (map.is_dictionary_map()) {
44 if (!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL) return false;
45 return access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad &&
46 map.object()->is_prototype_map();
47 }
48 return !map.object()->has_named_interceptor() &&
49 // TODO(verwaest): Allowlist contexts to which we have access.
50 !map.is_access_check_needed();
51 }
52 return false;
53}

55#ifdef DEBUG
56bool HasFieldRepresentationDependenciesOnMap(
57 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>& dependencies,
58 Handle<Map> const& field_owner_map) {
59 for (auto dep : dependencies) {
60 if (CompilationDependencies::IsFieldRepresentationDependencyOnMap(
61 dep, field_owner_map)) {
62 return true;
63 }
64 }
65 return false;
66}

72std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, AccessMode access_mode) {
73 switch (access_mode) {
74 case AccessMode::kLoad:
75 return os << "Load";
76 case AccessMode::kStore:
77 return os << "Store";
78 case AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
79 return os << "StoreInLiteral";
80 case AccessMode::kHas:
81 return os << "Has";
82 case AccessMode::kDefine:
83 return os << "Define";
84 }
85 UNREACHABLE();
86}

108// static
109PropertyAccessInfo PropertyAccessInfo::DataField(
110 JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
111 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>&& dependencies,
112 FieldIndex field_index, Representation field_representation,
113 Type field_type, MapRef field_owner_map, OptionalMapRef field_map,
114 OptionalJSObjectRef holder, OptionalMapRef transition_map) {
115 DCHECK(!field_representation.IsNone());
116 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
117 field_representation.IsDouble(),
118 HasFieldRepresentationDependenciesOnMap(
119 dependencies, transition_map.has_value() ? transition_map->object()
120 : holder.has_value() ? holder->map(broker).object()
121 : receiver_map.object()));
122 return PropertyAccessInfo(kDataField, holder, transition_map, field_index,
123 field_representation, field_type, field_owner_map,
124 field_map, {{receiver_map}, zone},
125 std::move(dependencies));
126}

128// static
129PropertyAccessInfo PropertyAccessInfo::FastDataConstant(
130 Zone* zone, MapRef receiver_map,
131 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*>&& dependencies,
132 FieldIndex field_index, Representation field_representation,
133 Type field_type, MapRef field_owner_map, OptionalMapRef field_map,
134 OptionalJSObjectRef holder, OptionalMapRef transition_map) {
135 DCHECK(!field_representation.IsNone());
136 return PropertyAccessInfo(kFastDataConstant, holder, transition_map,
137 field_index, field_representation, field_type,
138 field_owner_map, field_map, {{receiver_map}, zone},
139 std::move(dependencies));
140}

254template <class RefT>
255bool OptionalRefEquals(OptionalRef<RefT> lhs, OptionalRef<RefT> rhs) {
256 if (!lhs.has_value()) return !rhs.has_value();
257 if (!rhs.has_value()) return false;
258 return lhs->equals(rhs.value());
259}
260
261template <class T>
262void AppendVector(ZoneVector<T>* dst, const ZoneVector<T>& src) {
263 dst->insert(dst->end(), src.begin(), src.end());
264}

268bool PropertyAccessInfo::Merge(PropertyAccessInfo const* that,
269 AccessMode access_mode, Zone* zone) {
270 if (kind_ != that->kind_) return false;
271 if (!OptionalRefEquals(holder_, that->holder_)) return false;
272
273 switch (kind_) {
274 case kInvalid:
275 DCHECK_EQ(that->kind_, kInvalid);
276 return true;
277
278 case kDataField:
279 case kFastDataConstant: {
280 // Check if we actually access the same field (we use the
281 // GetFieldAccessStubKey method here just like the ICs do
282 // since that way we only compare the relevant bits of the
283 // field indices).
284 if (field_index_.GetFieldAccessStubKey() !=
285 that->field_index_.GetFieldAccessStubKey()) {
286 return false;
287 }
288
289 switch (access_mode) {
290 case AccessMode::kHas:
291 case AccessMode::kLoad: {
292 if (!field_representation_.Equals(that->field_representation_)) {
293 if (field_representation_.IsDouble() ||
294 that->field_representation_.IsDouble()) {
295 return false;
296 }
297 field_representation_ = Representation::Tagged();
298 }
299 if (!OptionalRefEquals(field_map_, that->field_map_)) {
300 field_map_ = {};
301 }
302 break;
303 }
304 case AccessMode::kStore:
305 case AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
306 case AccessMode::kDefine: {
307 // For stores, the field map and field representation information
308 // must match exactly, otherwise we cannot merge the stores. We
309 // also need to make sure that in case of transitioning stores,
310 // the transition targets match.
311 if (!OptionalRefEquals(field_map_, that->field_map_) ||
312 !field_representation_.Equals(that->field_representation_) ||
313 !OptionalRefEquals(transition_map_, that->transition_map_)) {
314 return false;
315 }
316 break;
317 }
318 }
319
320 field_type_ = Type::Union(field_type_, that->field_type_, zone);
321 AppendVector(&lookup_start_object_maps_, that->lookup_start_object_maps_);
322 AppendVector(&unrecorded_dependencies_, that->unrecorded_dependencies_);
323 return true;
324 }
325
326 case kDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant:
327 case kFastAccessorConstant: {
328 // Check if we actually access the same constant.
329 if (!OptionalRefEquals(constant_, that->constant_)) return false;
330
331 DCHECK(unrecorded_dependencies_.empty());
332 DCHECK(that->unrecorded_dependencies_.empty());
333 AppendVector(&lookup_start_object_maps_, that->lookup_start_object_maps_);
334 return true;
335 }
336
337 case kDictionaryProtoDataConstant: {
338 DCHECK_EQ(AccessMode::kLoad, access_mode);
339 if (dictionary_index_ != that->dictionary_index_) return false;
340 AppendVector(&lookup_start_object_maps_, that->lookup_start_object_maps_);
341 return true;
342 }
343
344 case kNotFound:
345 case kStringLength: {
346 DCHECK(unrecorded_dependencies_.empty());
347 DCHECK(that->unrecorded_dependencies_.empty());
348 AppendVector(&lookup_start_object_maps_, that->lookup_start_object_maps_);
349 return true;
350 }
351 case kModuleExport:
352 return false;
353 }
354}

364base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> AccessInfoFactory::ComputeElementAccessInfo(
365 MapRef map, AccessMode access_mode) const {
366 if (!map.CanInlineElementAccess()) return {};
367 return ElementAccessInfo({{map}, zone()}, map.elements_kind(), zone());
368}
369
370bool AccessInfoFactory::ComputeElementAccessInfos(
371 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback,
372 ZoneVector<ElementAccessInfo>* access_infos) const {
373 AccessMode access_mode = feedback.keyed_mode().access_mode();
374 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
375 // For polymorphic loads of similar elements kinds (i.e. all tagged or all
376 // double), always use the "worst case" code without a transition. This is
377 // much faster than transitioning the elements to the worst case, trading a
378 // TransitionElementsKind for a CheckMaps, avoiding mutation of the array.
379 base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> access_info =
380 ConsolidateElementLoad(feedback);
381 if (access_info.has_value()) {
382 access_infos->push_back(*access_info);
383 return true;
384 }
385 }
386
387 for (auto const& group : feedback.transition_groups()) {
388 DCHECK(!group.empty());
389 OptionalMapRef target = group.front();
390 base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> access_info =
391 ComputeElementAccessInfo(target.value(), access_mode);
392 if (!access_info.has_value()) return false;
393
394 for (size_t i = 1; i < group.size(); ++i) {
395 OptionalMapRef map_ref = group[i];
396 if (!map_ref.has_value()) continue;
397 access_info->AddTransitionSource(map_ref.value());
398 }
399 access_infos->push_back(*access_info);
400 }
401 return true;
402}

404PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::ComputeDataFieldAccessInfo(
405 MapRef receiver_map, MapRef map, NameRef name, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
406 InternalIndex descriptor, AccessMode access_mode) const {
407 DCHECK(descriptor.is_found());
408 // TODO(jgruber,v8:7790): Use DescriptorArrayRef instead.
409 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
410 map.instance_descriptors(broker()).object();
411 PropertyDetails const details = descriptors->GetDetails(descriptor);
412 int index = descriptors->GetFieldIndex(descriptor);
413 Representation details_representation = details.representation();
414 if (details_representation.IsNone()) {
415 // The ICs collect feedback in PREMONOMORPHIC state already,
416 // but at this point the {receiver_map} might still contain
417 // fields for which the representation has not yet been
418 // determined by the runtime. So we need to catch this case
419 // here and fall back to use the regular IC logic instead.
420 return Invalid();
421 }
422 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(*map.object(), index,
423 details_representation);
424 // Private brands are used when loading private methods, which are stored in a
425 // BlockContext, an internal object.
426 Type field_type = name.object()->IsPrivateBrand() ? Type::OtherInternal()
427 : Type::NonInternal();
428 OptionalMapRef field_map;
429
430 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*> unrecorded_dependencies(zone());
431
432 Handle<FieldType> descriptors_field_type =
433 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
434 descriptors->GetFieldType(descriptor));
435 OptionalObjectRef descriptors_field_type_ref =
436 TryMakeRef<Object>(broker(), descriptors_field_type);
437 if (!descriptors_field_type_ref.has_value()) return Invalid();
438
439 // Note: FindFieldOwner may be called multiple times throughout one
440 // compilation. This is safe since its result is fixed for a given map and
441 // descriptor.
442 MapRef field_owner_map = map.FindFieldOwner(broker(), descriptor);
443
444 if (details_representation.IsSmi()) {
445 field_type = Type::SignedSmall();
446 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
447 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
448 map, field_owner_map, descriptor, details_representation));
449 } else if (details_representation.IsDouble()) {
450 field_type = type_cache_->kFloat64;
451 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
452 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
453 map, field_owner_map, descriptor, details_representation));
454 } else if (details_representation.IsHeapObject()) {
455 if (IsNone(*descriptors_field_type)) {
456 switch (access_mode) {
457 case AccessMode::kStore:
458 case AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
459 case AccessMode::kDefine:
460 // Store is not safe if the field type was cleared.
461 return Invalid();
462 case AccessMode::kLoad:
463 case AccessMode::kHas:
464 break;
465 }
466
467 // The field type was cleared by the GC, so we don't know anything
468 // about the contents now.
469 }
470 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
471 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
472 map, field_owner_map, descriptor, details_representation));
473 if (IsClass(*descriptors_field_type)) {
474 // Remember the field map, and try to infer a useful type.
475 OptionalMapRef maybe_field_map =
476 TryMakeRef(broker(), FieldType::AsClass(*descriptors_field_type));
477 if (!maybe_field_map.has_value()) return Invalid();
478 field_type = Type::For(maybe_field_map.value(), broker());
479 field_map = maybe_field_map;
480 }
481 } else {
482 CHECK(details_representation.IsTagged());
483 }
484 // TODO(turbofan): We may want to do this only depending on the use
485 // of the access info.
486 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
487 dependencies()->FieldTypeDependencyOffTheRecord(
488 map, field_owner_map, descriptor,
489 descriptors_field_type_ref.value()));
490
491 PropertyConstness constness =
492 dependencies()->DependOnFieldConstness(map, field_owner_map, descriptor);
493
494 switch (constness) {
495 case PropertyConstness::kMutable:
496 return PropertyAccessInfo::DataField(
497 broker(), zone(), receiver_map, std::move(unrecorded_dependencies),
498 field_index, details_representation, field_type, field_owner_map,
499 field_map, holder, {});
500
501 case PropertyConstness::kConst:
502 return PropertyAccessInfo::FastDataConstant(
503 zone(), receiver_map, std::move(unrecorded_dependencies), field_index,
504 details_representation, field_type, field_owner_map, field_map,
505 holder, {});
506 }
507 UNREACHABLE();
508}

510namespace {

512using AccessorsObjectGetter = std::function<Handle<Object>()>;
513
514PropertyAccessInfo AccessorAccessInfoHelper(
515 Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone, JSHeapBroker* broker,
516 const AccessInfoFactory* ai_factory, MapRef receiver_map, NameRef name,
517 MapRef holder_map, OptionalJSObjectRef holder, AccessMode access_mode,
518 AccessorsObjectGetter get_accessors) {
519 if (holder_map.instance_type() == JS_MODULE_NAMESPACE_TYPE) {
520 DCHECK(holder_map.object()->is_prototype_map());
521 Handle<PrototypeInfo> proto_info = broker->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
522 PrototypeInfo::cast(holder_map.object()->prototype_info()));
523 Handle<JSModuleNamespace> module_namespace =
524 broker->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
525 JSModuleNamespace::cast(proto_info->module_namespace()));
526 Handle<Cell> cell = broker->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
527 Cell::cast(module_namespace->module()->exports()->Lookup(
528 isolate, name.object(),
529 Smi::ToInt(Object::GetHash(*name.object())))));
530 if (IsAnyStore(access_mode)) {
531 // ES#sec-module-namespace-exotic-objects-set-p-v-receiver
532 // ES#sec-module-namespace-exotic-objects-defineownproperty-p-desc
533 //
534 // Storing to a module namespace object is always an error or a no-op in
535 // JS.
536 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
537 }
538 if (IsTheHole(cell->value(kRelaxedLoad), isolate)) {
539 // This module has not been fully initialized yet.
540 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
541 }
542 OptionalCellRef cell_ref = TryMakeRef(broker, cell);
543 if (!cell_ref.has_value()) {
544 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
545 }
546 return PropertyAccessInfo::ModuleExport(zone, receiver_map,
547 cell_ref.value());
548 }
549 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
550 // kHas is not supported for dictionary mode objects.
551 DCHECK(!holder_map.is_dictionary_map());
552
553 // HasProperty checks don't call getter/setters, existence is sufficient.
554 return PropertyAccessInfo::FastAccessorConstant(zone, receiver_map, holder,
555 {}, {});
556 }
557 Handle<Object> maybe_accessors = get_accessors();
558 if (!IsAccessorPair(*maybe_accessors)) {
559 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
560 }
561 Handle<AccessorPair> accessors = Handle<AccessorPair>::cast(maybe_accessors);
562 Handle<Object> accessor = broker->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
563 access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad ? accessors->getter(kAcquireLoad)
564 : accessors->setter(kAcquireLoad));
565
566 OptionalObjectRef accessor_ref = TryMakeRef(broker, accessor);
567 if (!accessor_ref.has_value()) return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
568
569 OptionalJSObjectRef api_holder_ref;
570 if (!IsJSFunction(*accessor)) {
571 CallOptimization optimization(broker->local_isolate_or_isolate(), accessor);
572 if (!optimization.is_simple_api_call() ||
573 optimization.IsCrossContextLazyAccessorPair(
574 *broker->target_native_context().object(), *holder_map.object())) {
575 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
576 }
577 if (DEBUG_BOOL && holder.has_value()) {
578 base::Optional<Tagged<NativeContext>> holder_creation_context =
579 holder->object()->GetCreationContext();
580 CHECK(holder_creation_context.has_value());
581 CHECK_EQ(*broker->target_native_context().object(),
582 holder_creation_context.value());
583 }
584
585 CallOptimization::HolderLookup holder_lookup;
586 Handle<JSObject> api_holder = broker->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
587 optimization.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(
588 broker->local_isolate_or_isolate(), receiver_map.object(),
589 &holder_lookup));
590 if (holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
591 return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
592 }
593 DCHECK_IMPLIES(holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver,
594 api_holder.is_null());
595 DCHECK_IMPLIES(holder_lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound,
596 !api_holder.is_null());
597
598 if (!api_holder.is_null()) {
599 api_holder_ref = TryMakeRef(broker, api_holder);
600 if (!api_holder_ref.has_value()) return PropertyAccessInfo::Invalid(zone);
601 }
602 }
603 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad) {
604 base::Optional<Tagged<Name>> cached_property_name =
605 FunctionTemplateInfo::TryGetCachedPropertyName(isolate, *accessor);
606 if (cached_property_name.has_value()) {
607 OptionalNameRef cached_property_name_ref =
608 TryMakeRef(broker, cached_property_name.value());
609 if (cached_property_name_ref.has_value()) {
610 PropertyAccessInfo access_info = ai_factory->ComputePropertyAccessInfo(
611 holder_map, cached_property_name_ref.value(), access_mode);
612 if (!access_info.IsInvalid()) return access_info;
613 }
614 }
615 }
616
617 if (holder_map.is_dictionary_map()) {
618 CHECK(!api_holder_ref.has_value());
619 return PropertyAccessInfo::DictionaryProtoAccessorConstant(
620 zone, receiver_map, holder, accessor_ref.value(), api_holder_ref, name);
621 } else {
622 return PropertyAccessInfo::FastAccessorConstant(
623 zone, receiver_map, holder, accessor_ref.value(), api_holder_ref);
624 }
625}

629PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::ComputeAccessorDescriptorAccessInfo(
630 MapRef receiver_map, NameRef name, MapRef holder_map,
631 OptionalJSObjectRef holder, InternalIndex descriptor,
632 AccessMode access_mode) const {
633 DCHECK(descriptor.is_found());
634 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
635 holder_map.object()->instance_descriptors(kRelaxedLoad));
636 SLOW_DCHECK(descriptor ==
637 descriptors->Search(*name.object(), *holder_map.object(), true));
638
639 auto get_accessors = [&]() {
640 return broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
641 descriptors->GetStrongValue(descriptor));
642 };
643 return AccessorAccessInfoHelper(isolate(), zone(), broker(), this,
644 receiver_map, name, holder_map, holder,
645 access_mode, get_accessors);
646}
647
648PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::ComputeDictionaryProtoAccessInfo(
649 MapRef receiver_map, NameRef name, JSObjectRef holder,
650 InternalIndex dictionary_index, AccessMode access_mode,
651 PropertyDetails details) const {
652 CHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
653 DCHECK(holder.map(broker()).object()->is_prototype_map());
654 DCHECK_EQ(access_mode, AccessMode::kLoad);
655
656 // We can only inline accesses to constant properties.
657 if (details.constness() != PropertyConstness::kConst) {
658 return Invalid();
659 }
660
661 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
662 return PropertyAccessInfo::DictionaryProtoDataConstant(
663 zone(), receiver_map, holder, dictionary_index, name);
664 }
665
666 auto get_accessors = [&]() {
667 return JSObject::DictionaryPropertyAt(isolate(), holder.object(),
668 dictionary_index);
669 };
670 return AccessorAccessInfoHelper(isolate(), zone(), broker(), this,
671 receiver_map, name, holder.map(broker()),
672 holder, access_mode, get_accessors);
673}
674
675bool AccessInfoFactory::TryLoadPropertyDetails(
676 MapRef map, OptionalJSObjectRef maybe_holder, NameRef name,
677 InternalIndex* index_out, PropertyDetails* details_out) const {
678 if (map.is_dictionary_map()) {
679 DCHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
680 DCHECK(map.object()->is_prototype_map());
681
682 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
683
684 if (!maybe_holder.has_value()) {
685 // TODO(v8:11457) In this situation, we have a dictionary mode prototype
686 // as a receiver. Consider other means of obtaining the holder in this
687 // situation.
688
689 // Without the holder, we can't get the property details.
690 return false;
691 }
692
693 Handle<JSObject> holder = maybe_holder->object();
694 if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
695 Tagged<SwissNameDictionary> dict = holder->property_dictionary_swiss();
696 *index_out = dict->FindEntry(isolate(), name.object());
697 if (index_out->is_found()) {
698 *details_out = dict->DetailsAt(*index_out);
699 }
700 } else {
701 Tagged<NameDictionary> dict = holder->property_dictionary();
702 *index_out = dict->FindEntry(isolate(), name.object());
703 if (index_out->is_found()) {
704 *details_out = dict->DetailsAt(*index_out);
705 }
706 }
707 } else {
708 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
709 *map.instance_descriptors(broker()).object();
710 *index_out = descriptors->Search(*name.object(), *map.object(), true);
711 if (index_out->is_found()) {
712 *details_out = descriptors->GetDetails(*index_out);
713 }
714 }
715
716 return true;
717}
718
719PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::ComputePropertyAccessInfo(
720 MapRef map, NameRef name, AccessMode access_mode) const {
721 CHECK(name.IsUniqueName());
722
723 // Dictionary property const tracking is unsupported with concurrent inlining.
724 CHECK(!V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
725
726 JSHeapBroker::MapUpdaterGuardIfNeeded mumd_scope(broker());
727
728 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas && !IsJSReceiverMap(*map.object())) {
729 return Invalid();
730 }
731
732 // Check if it is safe to inline property access for the {map}.
733 if (!CanInlinePropertyAccess(map, access_mode)) {
734 return Invalid();
735 }
736
737 // We support fast inline cases for certain JSObject getters.
738 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
739 PropertyAccessInfo access_info = LookupSpecialFieldAccessor(map, name);
740 if (!access_info.IsInvalid()) return access_info;
741 }
742
743 // Only relevant if V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING enabled.
744 bool dictionary_prototype_on_chain = false;
745 bool fast_mode_prototype_on_chain = false;
746
747 // Remember the receiver map. We use {map} as loop variable.
748 MapRef receiver_map = map;
749 OptionalJSObjectRef holder;
750
751 // Perform the implicit ToObject for primitives here.
752 // Implemented according to ES6 section 7.3.2 GetV (V, P).
753 // Note: Keep sync'd with
754 // CompilationDependencies::DependOnStablePrototypeChains.
755 if (receiver_map.IsPrimitiveMap()) {
756 OptionalJSFunctionRef constructor =
757 broker()->target_native_context().GetConstructorFunction(broker(),
758 receiver_map);
759 if (!constructor.has_value()) return Invalid();
760 map = constructor->initial_map(broker());
761 DCHECK(!map.IsPrimitiveMap());
762 }
763
764 while (true) {
765 PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty();
766 InternalIndex index = InternalIndex::NotFound();
767 if (!TryLoadPropertyDetails(map, holder, name, &index, &details)) {
768 return Invalid();
769 }
770
771 if (index.is_found()) {
772 if (IsAnyStore(access_mode)) {
773 DCHECK(!map.is_dictionary_map());
774
775 // Don't bother optimizing stores to read-only properties.
776 if (details.IsReadOnly()) return Invalid();
777
778 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData && holder.has_value()) {
779 // This is a store to a property not found on the receiver but on a
780 // prototype. According to ES6 section 9.1.9 [[Set]], we need to
781 // create a new data property on the receiver. We can still optimize
782 // if such a transition already exists.
783 return LookupTransition(receiver_map, name, holder, NONE);
784 }
785 }
786
787 if (IsDefiningStore(access_mode)) {
788 if (details.attributes() != PropertyAttributes::NONE) {
789 // We should store the property with WEC attributes, but that's not the
790 // attributes of the property that we found. We just bail out and let
791 // the runtime figure out what to do (which probably requires changing
792 // the object's map).
793 return Invalid();
794 }
795 }
796
797 if (map.is_dictionary_map()) {
798 DCHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
799
800 if (fast_mode_prototype_on_chain) {
801 // TODO(v8:11248) While the work on dictionary mode prototypes is in
802 // progress, we may still see fast mode objects on the chain prior to
803 // reaching a dictionary mode prototype holding the property . Due to
804 // this only being an intermediate state, we don't stupport these kind
805 // of heterogenous prototype chains.
806 return Invalid();
807 }
808
809 // TryLoadPropertyDetails only succeeds if we know the holder.
810 return ComputeDictionaryProtoAccessInfo(
811 receiver_map, name, holder.value(), index, access_mode, details);
812 }
813
814 if (dictionary_prototype_on_chain) {
815 // If V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL was disabled, then a
816 // dictionary prototype would have caused a bailout earlier.
817 DCHECK(V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL);
818
819 // TODO(v8:11248) We have a fast mode holder, but there was a dictionary
820 // mode prototype earlier on the chain. Note that seeing a fast mode
821 // prototype even though V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING is enabled
822 // should only be possible while the implementation of dictionary mode
823 // prototypes is work in progress. Eventually, enabling
824 // V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING will guarantee that all prototypes
825 // are always in dictionary mode, making this case unreachable. However,
826 // due to the complications of checking dictionary mode prototypes for
827 // modification, we don't attempt to support dictionary mode prototypes
828 // occuring before a fast mode holder on the chain.
829 return Invalid();
830 }
831 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
832 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
833 return ComputeDataFieldAccessInfo(receiver_map, map, name, holder,
834 index, access_mode);
835 } else {
836 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
837 // TODO(turbofan): Add support for general accessors?
838 return Invalid();
839 }
840 } else {
841 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
842 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
843 return ComputeAccessorDescriptorAccessInfo(receiver_map, name, map,
844 holder, index, access_mode);
845 }
846
847 UNREACHABLE();
848 }
849
850 // The property wasn't found on {map}. Look on the prototype if appropriate.
851 DCHECK(!index.is_found());
852
853 // Don't search on the prototype chain for special indices in case of
854 // integer indexed exotic objects (see ES6 section 9.4.5).
855 if (IsJSTypedArrayMap(*map.object()) && name.IsString()) {
856 StringRef name_str = name.AsString();
857 SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(
858 *name_str.object(), broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate());
859 if (IsSpecialIndex(*name_str.object(), access_guard)) return Invalid();
860 }
861
862 // Don't search on the prototype when storing in literals, or performing a
863 // Define operation
864 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral ||
865 access_mode == AccessMode::kDefine) {
866 PropertyAttributes attrs = NONE;
867 if (name.object()->IsPrivate()) {
868 // When PrivateNames are added to an object, they are by definition
869 // non-enumerable.
870 attrs = DONT_ENUM;
871 }
872 return LookupTransition(receiver_map, name, holder, attrs);
873 }
874
875 // Don't lookup private symbols on the prototype chain.
876 if (name.object()->IsPrivate()) {
877 return Invalid();
878 }
879
880 if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL && holder.has_value()) {
881 // At this point, we are past the first loop iteration.
882 DCHECK(holder->object()->map()->is_prototype_map());
883 DCHECK(!holder->map(broker()).equals(receiver_map));
884
885 fast_mode_prototype_on_chain =
886 fast_mode_prototype_on_chain || !map.is_dictionary_map();
887 dictionary_prototype_on_chain =
888 dictionary_prototype_on_chain || map.is_dictionary_map();
889 }
890
891 // Walk up the prototype chain.
892 // Load the map's prototype's map to guarantee that every time we use it,
893 // we use the same Map.
894 HeapObjectRef prototype = map.prototype(broker());
895
896 MapRef map_prototype_map = prototype.map(broker());
897 if (!IsJSObjectMap(*map_prototype_map.object())) {
898 // Don't allow proxies on the prototype chain.
899 if (!prototype.IsNull()) {
900 DCHECK(IsJSProxy(*prototype.object()) ||
901 IsWasmObject(*prototype.object()));
902 return Invalid();
903 }
904
905 DCHECK(prototype.IsNull());
906
907 if (dictionary_prototype_on_chain) {
908 // TODO(v8:11248) See earlier comment about
909 // dictionary_prototype_on_chain. We don't support absent properties
910 // with dictionary mode prototypes on the chain, either. This is again
911 // just due to how we currently deal with dependencies for dictionary
912 // properties during finalization.
913 return Invalid();
914 }
915
916 // Store to property not found on the receiver or any prototype, we need
917 // to transition to a new data property.
918 // Implemented according to ES6 section 9.1.9 [[Set]] (P, V, Receiver)
919 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
920 return LookupTransition(receiver_map, name, holder, NONE);
921 }
922
923 // The property was not found (access returns undefined or throws
924 // depending on the language mode of the load operation.
925 // Implemented according to ES6 section 9.1.8 [[Get]] (P, Receiver)
926 return PropertyAccessInfo::NotFound(zone(), receiver_map, holder);
927 }
928
929 holder = prototype.AsJSObject();
930 map = map_prototype_map;
931
932 if (!CanInlinePropertyAccess(map, access_mode)) {
933 return Invalid();
934 }
935
936 // Successful lookup on prototype chain needs to guarantee that all the
937 // prototypes up to the holder have stable maps, except for dictionary-mode
938 // prototypes. We currently do this by taking a
939 // DependOnStablePrototypeChains dependency in the caller.
940 //
941 // TODO(jgruber): This is brittle and easy to miss. Consider a refactor
942 // that moves the responsibility of taking the dependency into
943 // AccessInfoFactory.
944 }
945 UNREACHABLE();
946}

948PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(
949 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos, AccessMode access_mode) const {
950 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> merged_access_infos(zone());
951 MergePropertyAccessInfos(access_infos, access_mode, &merged_access_infos);
952 if (merged_access_infos.size() == 1) {
953 PropertyAccessInfo& result = merged_access_infos.front();
954 if (!result.IsInvalid()) {
955 result.RecordDependencies(dependencies());
956 return result;
957 }
958 }
959 return Invalid();
960}

962void PropertyAccessInfo::RecordDependencies(
963 CompilationDependencies* dependencies) {
964 for (CompilationDependency const* d : unrecorded_dependencies_) {
965 dependencies->RecordDependency(d);
966 }
967 unrecorded_dependencies_.clear();
968}
969
970bool AccessInfoFactory::FinalizePropertyAccessInfos(
971 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos, AccessMode access_mode,
972 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo>* result) const {
973 if (access_infos.empty()) return false;
974 MergePropertyAccessInfos(access_infos, access_mode, result);
975 for (PropertyAccessInfo const& info : *result) {
976 if (info.IsInvalid()) return false;
977 }
978 for (PropertyAccessInfo& info : *result) {
979 info.RecordDependencies(dependencies());
980 }
981 return true;
982}
983
984void AccessInfoFactory::MergePropertyAccessInfos(
985 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> infos, AccessMode access_mode,
986 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo>* result) const {
987 DCHECK(result->empty());
988 for (auto it = infos.begin(), end = infos.end(); it != end; ++it) {
989 bool merged = false;
990 for (auto ot = it + 1; ot != end; ++ot) {
991 if (ot->Merge(&(*it), access_mode, zone())) {
992 merged = true;
993 break;
994 }
995 }
996 if (!merged) result->push_back(*it);
997 }
998 CHECK(!result->empty());
999}

1008Maybe<ElementsKind> GeneralizeElementsKind(ElementsKind this_kind,
1009 ElementsKind that_kind) {
1010 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(this_kind)) {
1011 that_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(that_kind);
1012 } else if (IsHoleyElementsKind(that_kind)) {
1013 this_kind = GetHoleyElementsKind(this_kind);
1014 }
1015 if (this_kind == that_kind) return Just(this_kind);
1016 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(that_kind) == IsDoubleElementsKind(this_kind)) {
1017 if (IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(that_kind, this_kind)) {
1018 return Just(this_kind);
1019 }
1020 if (IsMoreGeneralElementsKindTransition(this_kind, that_kind)) {
1021 return Just(that_kind);
1022 }
1023 }
1024 return Nothing<ElementsKind>();
1025}

1029base::Optional<ElementAccessInfo> AccessInfoFactory::ConsolidateElementLoad(
1030 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback) const {
1031 if (feedback.transition_groups().empty()) return {};
1032
1033 DCHECK(!feedback.transition_groups().front().empty());
1034 MapRef first_map = feedback.transition_groups().front().front();
1035 InstanceType instance_type = first_map.instance_type();
1036 ElementsKind elements_kind = first_map.elements_kind();
1037
1038 ZoneVector<MapRef> maps(zone());
1039 for (auto const& group : feedback.transition_groups()) {
1040 for (MapRef map : group) {
1041 if (map.instance_type() != instance_type ||
1042 !map.CanInlineElementAccess()) {
1043 return {};
1044 }
1045 if (!GeneralizeElementsKind(elements_kind, map.elements_kind())
1046 .To(&elements_kind)) {
1047 return {};
1048 }
1049 maps.push_back(map);
1050 }
1051 }
1052
1053 return ElementAccessInfo(std::move(maps), elements_kind, zone());
1054}
1055
1056PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::LookupSpecialFieldAccessor(
1057 MapRef map, NameRef name) const {
1058 // Check for String::length field accessor.
1059 if (IsStringMap(*map.object())) {
1060 if (Name::Equals(isolate(), name.object(),
1061 isolate()->factory()->length_string())) {
1062 return PropertyAccessInfo::StringLength(zone(), map);
1063 }
1064 return Invalid();
1065 }
1066 // Check for special JSObject field accessors.
1067 FieldIndex field_index;
1068 if (Accessors::IsJSObjectFieldAccessor(isolate(), map.object(), name.object(),
1069 &field_index)) {
1070 Type field_type = Type::NonInternal();
1071 Representation field_representation = Representation::Tagged();
1072 if (IsJSArrayMap(*map.object())) {
1073 DCHECK(Name::Equals(isolate(), isolate()->factory()->length_string(),
1074 name.object()));
1075 // The JSArray::length property is a smi in the range
1076 // [0, FixedDoubleArray::kMaxLength] in case of fast double
1077 // elements, a smi in the range [0, FixedArray::kMaxLength]
1078 // in case of other fast elements, and [0, kMaxUInt32] in
1079 // case of other arrays.
1080 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(map.elements_kind())) {
1081 field_type = type_cache_->kFixedDoubleArrayLengthType;
1082 field_representation = Representation::Smi();
1083 } else if (IsFastElementsKind(map.elements_kind())) {
1084 field_type = type_cache_->kFixedArrayLengthType;
1085 field_representation = Representation::Smi();
1086 } else {
1087 field_type = type_cache_->kJSArrayLengthType;
1088 }
1089 }
1090 // Special fields are always mutable.
1091 return PropertyAccessInfo::DataField(broker(), zone(), map, {{}, zone()},
1092 field_index, field_representation,
1093 field_type, map, {}, {}, {});
1094 }
1095 return Invalid();
1096}
1097
1098PropertyAccessInfo AccessInfoFactory::LookupTransition(
1099 MapRef map, NameRef name, OptionalJSObjectRef holder,
1100 PropertyAttributes attrs) const {
1101 // Check if the {map} has a data transition with the given {name}.
1102 Tagged<Map> transition =
1103 TransitionsAccessor(isolate(), *map.object(), true)
1104 .SearchTransition(*name.object(), PropertyKind::kData, attrs);
1105 if (transition.is_null()) return Invalid();
1106 OptionalMapRef maybe_transition_map = TryMakeRef(broker(), transition);
1107 if (!maybe_transition_map.has_value()) return Invalid();
1108 MapRef transition_map = maybe_transition_map.value();
1109
1110 InternalIndex const number = transition_map.object()->LastAdded();
1111 Handle<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
1112 transition_map.instance_descriptors(broker()).object();
1113 PropertyDetails const details = descriptors->GetDetails(number);
1114
1115 // Don't bother optimizing stores to read-only properties.
1116 if (details.IsReadOnly()) return Invalid();
1117
1118 // TODO(bmeurer): Handle transition to data constant?
1119 if (details.location() != PropertyLocation::kField) return Invalid();
1120
1121 int const index = details.field_index();
1122 Representation details_representation = details.representation();
1123 if (details_representation.IsNone()) return Invalid();
1124
1125 FieldIndex field_index = FieldIndex::ForPropertyIndex(
1126 *transition_map.object(), index, details_representation);
1127 Type field_type = Type::NonInternal();
1128 OptionalMapRef field_map;
1129
1130 DCHECK_EQ(transition_map, transition_map.FindFieldOwner(broker(), number));
1131
1132 ZoneVector<CompilationDependency const*> unrecorded_dependencies(zone());
1133 if (details_representation.IsSmi()) {
1134 field_type = Type::SignedSmall();
1135 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
1136 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
1137 transition_map, transition_map, number, details_representation));
1138 } else if (details_representation.IsDouble()) {
1139 field_type = type_cache_->kFloat64;
1140 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
1141 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
1142 transition_map, transition_map, number, details_representation));
1143 } else if (details_representation.IsHeapObject()) {
1144 // Extract the field type from the property details (make sure its
1145 // representation is TaggedPointer to reflect the heap object case).
1146 // TODO(jgruber,v8:7790): Use DescriptorArrayRef instead.
1147 Handle<FieldType> descriptors_field_type =
1148 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(descriptors->GetFieldType(number));
1149 OptionalObjectRef descriptors_field_type_ref =
1150 TryMakeRef<Object>(broker(), descriptors_field_type);
1151 if (!descriptors_field_type_ref.has_value()) return Invalid();
1152
1153 if (IsNone(*descriptors_field_type)) {
1154 // Store is not safe if the field type was cleared.
1155 return Invalid();
1156 }
1157 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
1158 dependencies()->FieldRepresentationDependencyOffTheRecord(
1159 transition_map, transition_map, number, details_representation));
1160 if (IsClass(*descriptors_field_type)) {
1161 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
1162 dependencies()->FieldTypeDependencyOffTheRecord(
1163 transition_map, transition_map, number,
1164 *descriptors_field_type_ref));
1165 // Remember the field map, and try to infer a useful type.
1166 OptionalMapRef maybe_field_map =
1167 TryMakeRef(broker(), FieldType::AsClass(*descriptors_field_type));
1168 if (!maybe_field_map.has_value()) return Invalid();
1169 field_type = Type::For(maybe_field_map.value(), broker());
1170 field_map = maybe_field_map;
1171 }
1172 }
1173
1174 unrecorded_dependencies.push_back(
1175 dependencies()->TransitionDependencyOffTheRecord(transition_map));
1176 // Transitioning stores *may* store to const fields. The resulting
1177 // DataConstant access infos can be distinguished from later, i.e. redundant,
1178 // stores to the same constant field by the presence of a transition map.
1179 switch (dependencies()->DependOnFieldConstness(transition_map, transition_map,
1180 number)) {
1181 case PropertyConstness::kMutable:
1182 return PropertyAccessInfo::DataField(
1183 broker(), zone(), map, std::move(unrecorded_dependencies),
1184 field_index, details_representation, field_type, transition_map,
1185 field_map, holder, transition_map);
1186 case PropertyConstness::kConst:
1187 return PropertyAccessInfo::FastDataConstant(
1188 zone(), map, std::move(unrecorded_dependencies), field_index,
1189 details_representation, field_type, transition_map, field_map, holder,
1190 transition_map);
1191 }
1192 UNREACHABLE();
1193}
